h3. Summary

Pasting a code block from a plain text file to the comment field doesn't keep the text in plain text
h3. Environment
 * Cloud

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 * Create a multi-line code block on a plain text file. E.g:
{noformat}
function doSomething(param1, param2) { 
	console.log(param1);
	console.log(param2);

	// INC-1234
	var param3 = param2; 
	console.log(param3);
	
	// INC-884
	var param4 = param1; 
	console.log(param4);

	//INC-4261
	var param5 = param3; 
	console.log(param5);
}{noformat}

 * Copy the text
 * Paste the text to the comment box of an issue.

h3. Expected Results

The code block that is pasted should be in plain text
h3. Actual Results

The code block is pasted with some lines in the code snippet format and others as plain text

!Screen Shot 2021-05-28 at 12.52.47.png|thumbnail!
h3. Workaround

None

h1. Intro


When using Jira Expressions I want to be able to use a JavaScript like syntax for Nullish coalescing and optional chaining. ( ?? & ?. )

This can for example be useful when one expression is used to map different custom field values from multiple issue types.
h1. Current solution
{code:java}
(issue.issueType.id == 10021 && issue.customfield_10039 ? issue.customfield_10039.value : '') + 
(issue.issueType.id == 10012 && issue.customfield_10045 ? issue.customfield_10045.value : '' )
{code}
h1. Desired solution
{code:java}
issue.customfield_10039?.value ?? issue.customfield_10045?.value ?? ''
{code}

h3. Issue Summary

When using the REST API endpoint:
[https://YOUT_INSTANCE.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/notificationscheme|https://yout_instance.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/notificationscheme] it will retrieve all notification schemes even from projects which are in the trash. The problem here is that there is no way to distinguish the next gen notification schemes from the normal ones because after moving next gen project to the trash the end point will remove the scope property from the response.
h3. Steps to Reproduce

*Before moving next-gen project to the trash:*
{code:java}
{{
   "maxResults":50,
   "startAt":0,
   "total":2,
   "isLast":true,
   "values":[
      {
         "expand":"notificationSchemeEvents,user,group,projectRole,field,all",
         "id":10000,
         "self":"https://YOUT_INSTANCE.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/notificationscheme/10000",
         "name":"Default Notification Scheme"
      },
      {
         "expand":"notificationSchemeEvents,user,group,projectRole,field,all",
         "id":10293,
         "self":"YOUT_INSTANCE.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/notificationscheme/10293",
         "name":"NGP: Simplified Notification Scheme",
         "scope":{
            "type":"PROJECT",
            "project":{
               "id":"10360"
            }
         }
      }
   ]
}
{code}
*After moving next-gen project to the trash***
{code:java}
{
   "maxResults":50,
   "startAt":0,
   "total":2,
   "isLast":true,
   "values":[
      {
         "expand":"notificationSchemeEvents,user,group,projectRole,field,all",
         "id":10000,
         "self":"https://YOUT_INSTANCE.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/notificationscheme/10000",
         "name":"Default Notification Scheme"
      },
      {
         "expand":"notificationSchemeEvents,user,group,projectRole,field,all",
         "id":10293,
         "self":"https://YOUT_INSTANCEatlassian.net/rest/api/3/notificationscheme/10293",
         "name":"NGP: Simplified Notification Scheme"
      }
   ]
}{code}
h3. Expected Results

The response payload should not contain the notification schemes from next gen projects which are moved to the trash. This is the behavior for workflows and issue types for next gen projects it would be awesome to have the same behavior here as well.
h3. Actual Results

The response contains scoped notification schemes for next-gen projects that are trashed.
h3. Workaround

For the moment there is no way to distinguish Notification scheme from next-gen project in the trash and normal notifcation scheme so there is no known workaround.

h3. Issue Summary

While setting a field with API, if the text contains HTML, the code is added to the field and no conversion is done.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Try creating an issue using the description below:
{code:java}
"description": {
      "type": "doc",
      "version": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "This is <b>a test</b> description.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }{code}

h3. Expected Results
HTML is converted.
On the example above 'a test' would be *bold*.

h3. Actual Results
HTML is not converted and field has the description {code}This is <b>a test</b> description.{code}

h3. Workaround
N/A
